      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a rather ominous scenario. Having the assistant \"check in\" on you and micro-managing your work can definitely feel controlling and suffocating. It's possible that the company is trying to preemptively curb any future dissent or pushback by placing you under close supervision. This tactic is sometimes described as \" silently silencing\" or \" controlling behavior\" and can be a stark warning to others that speaking up won't be tolerated.",
      "source": "target",
